fields.descriptive_line: A set of 61 rings used by a woman of one of the hill tribes of Kachin State northern Burma to secure her <font -i>pukhang</font> (wrap-skirts). Black thitsi lacquered bamboo. c. early 20th century.
fields.physical_description: Set of large bamboo rings finished with black thitsi lacquer.  Used to secure a woman's "pukhang" (wrap around skirt)
fields.materials_techniques: Bamboo. Thitsi lacquer. Dye. Shaping. Lacquering. Dyeing.

fields.name: South and South East Asian Collection

fields.history_note: Such numbers of rings are used to secure a woman's <font -i>pukhang</font> (wrap skirt).
